7
00:00:34,960 --> 00:00:41,739
And the Party is giving itself the best birthday
present of all: the gift of changing its own

8
00:00:41,739 --> 00:00:43,280
past.

9
00:00:43,280 --> 00:00:48,280
Like any 100-year old, the Chinese Communist
Party wants to look good on its big day.

10
00:00:48,280 --> 00:00:53,550
So Party officials don’t like it when people
bring up all the mistakes they made before.

11
00:00:53,550 --> 00:00:57,309
In Party-speak, they call this “historical
nihilism.”

12
00:00:57,309 --> 00:01:02,679
Historical nihilism is anything that questions
the Party’s official rainbows-and-sunshine

13
00:01:02,679 --> 00:01:04,949
version of its past.

14
00:01:04,949 --> 00:01:09,620
Because questioning the Party’s past also
“means denying the ‘inevitability’ of

15
00:01:09,620 --> 00:01:13,030
China’s march towards socialism.”

16
00:01:13,030 --> 00:01:19,080
Chinese leader Xi Jinping blames historical
nihilism for the collapse of the Soviet Union.

17
00:01:19,080 --> 00:01:23,420
And he’s determined that’s not going to
happen to the Chinese Communist Party.

18
00:01:23,420 --> 00:01:28,480
Which is why earlier this year, the Party
launched a hotline for people to report any

19
00:01:28,480 --> 00:01:31,860
